free: #e It was night already, and the kid was sitting on his chair.
#c 已經晚上了，然後這個小孩正坐在他的椅子上。
#e (He) was (sitting) next to his bed in his room, watching his dog playing, and looking at a frog.
#c (他坐) 在房間裡的床舖旁邊，一面看著他的狗玩耍，一面看著一隻青蛙。
#e In the morning, the kid got up from bed.
#c 到了早上了，小孩起床了。
#e Well, no, that's not right. He is still sleeping. At night, this kid goes to sleep on the bed in his room.
#c 咦？不對。他還在睡覺。晚上的時候，這個小孩在他的房間裡上床睡覺。
#e There, the dog is also beside him, sleeping together. The frog is also there, sleeping by itself. It's just like that.
#c 在那邊呢，狗也在他旁邊一起睡覺。青蛙也在一旁自己睡覺。
#e In the morning, the kid and his dog get up.
#c 到了早上，小孩和他的狗都起床了。
#e They are looking towards the window, looking at the view outside.
#c 他們都在往窗外看外面的景色。
#e The kid is playing with his dog, teasing him, and deliberately throwing his shoes to him.
#c 小孩在跟狗玩耍、逗牠、故意拿鞋子丟牠。
#e Afterwards, the kid and the dog poke their heads out of the window.
#c 後來呢，小孩和狗便向窗外探頭。
#e The kid was looking outward from the window, and the dog ran to the outside.
#c 小孩從窗戶往外看，而小狗則跑到了外面去。
#e They went to bring, wait, what? There were trees and grass (outside), and the dog ran to go play out there.
#c 他們去拿，啊什麼啊？(外面)那邊有樹和草。而小狗是要跑到外面去玩。
#e (The child) went out to hug his dog, (the two) playing and chasing each other to the back of the house.
#c (小孩) 到外面去抱住他的狗，一面玩耍、一面追逐跑到屋後。
#e As they go to the back of the house, the kid starts calling out, and the dog is also barking to call out.
#c 來到了房子的後面呢，小孩便開始呼喊，小狗也跟著吠叫呼喊著。
#n 此處kiyoko 應為kiya ka "所以"。
#e Farther away, there was a tree right across from the house. There was a hole in the tree, where there was a beehive.
#c 在更遠處，房子的對面有一棵樹。樹上有一個洞，裡面有顆蜂窩。
#e So the kid and the dog went to the root of the tree.
#c 所以小孩和狗就前往，到達了樹根處。
#e They were looking at the beehive. There were bees flying out of it.
#c 他們看著蜂窩。裡面有蜜蜂正飛出來。
#e The dog is preparing to climb up to the tree, barking at all the bees that are flying out. The kid is shocked, as the bees are about to bite him and the frog.
#c 狗正準備要爬到樹上，對著所有飛出來的蜜蜂吠叫著。很多蜜蜂飛出來要叮咬小孩和青蛙，小孩便嚇了一大跳。
#n 此處第一個skyui 應為說者口誤。
#e After they hit down the beehive, the dog looked up at the tree, and so did the frog.
#c 他們把蜂巢打落之後，狗就往樹上看，連青蛙也是。
#e Then they went to look again to the other side of the mountains.
#c 接著他們又往山的另一邊看。
#e There is a big tree at a shalow slope, and there is hole in the tree.
#c 在某處緩坡的地方有一棵大樹，樹上有一個洞穴。
#n ini klai 為固定用語，有 "沒想到"、"突然"的語意。
#e The kid climbed up the tree to look at the whole, and all of a sudden an owl came out of that hole.
#c 小孩爬到樹上看洞穴，突然從洞穴裡跑出一隻貓頭鷹。
#e Seeing (the owl), the kid is shocked, and falls from the cliff. The dog runs to see the child, who is falling.
#c 看到了(貓頭鷹)後，小孩嚇了一跳，然後就從山坡上跌了下去。然後狗便跑去看正掉落的小孩。
#e Then, the owl comes flying again.
#c 然後，貓頭鷹又飛過來。
#e Being shocked, the kid was afraid, and said "It is coming to bite us! It is coming to peck on our heads!"
#c 小孩嚇了一跳，心理很害怕，說：「牠要來咬我們了！牠要來啄我們的頭了！」
#e The kid covered his head, and could only hide by climbing up to a large stone.
#c 小孩把頭擋住，只好爬到一個大石頭上面躲起來。
#e The owl searched (standing) on a tree branch, and saw the kid, who was sitting by himself below the tree root, and below the stone. The dog was there, too.
#c 貓頭鷹(站)在樹枝上眺望，看到了小孩，獨自坐在樹枝下和石頭下。狗也在那裏。
#e The owl still sat on the branch, looking at them.
#c 貓頭鷹還駐足在樹枝上看他們。
#e (The kid) climbed up the stone, and ended up riding on the head of something. I forgot.
#c (小孩) 爬到石頭上，結果騎到了一個東西的頭上。我忘記了。
#e He went riding on the head of an animal.
#c 他騎到了一個動物的頭上。
#n camac 專指 "四隻腳的野生動物"。
#e He ends up riding on the head of an animal.
#c 他騎到了一個動物的頭上。
#e The animal is running.
#c 這隻動物在跑。
#e It might be different. I forgot this part. I forgot.
#c 不一樣吧。忘了這個。忘記了。
#e This deer runs to the edge of a cliff.
#c 這隻鹿跑到懸崖邊。
#e The kid fell from the cliff down into some water, which was sort of like a lake.
#c 小孩從懸崖摔落，掉到了某個像是湖的水裡去。
#e He fell into the lake.
#c 他掉到了湖裡。
#e The were trees growing on the side of the cliff, from which the child fell. The deer watched from the top.
#c 懸崖上長滿了樹。小孩從上面跌了下去，而鹿則在上面看著。
#e Both he and the dog fell into the lake together.
#c 小孩和狗都一起掉到湖裡去了。
#e The kid lifted up the dog, and let the dog ride on this head, his shoulders.
#c 小孩把狗提起來，讓他騎在頭上、肩膀上。
#e So the kid went carrying his dog to look at the tree again.
#c 小孩背著他的狗，又去看樹。
#e He says to his dog: "Don't speak! Don't make any noise!".
#c 他對著他的狗說：「別說話！別出聲！」
#e The kid and the dog climbed up to the tree that had fallen to see (what was there in) its back.
#c 小孩和狗爬到了這棵已經倒了的樹上，去看樹的後面(有什麼)。
#e They went to look at the back of the tree, and saw two frogs over there.
#c 他們去看樹的後面，然後看到有兩隻青蛙在那裡。
#n 此處 wawaga 應為口誤。
#e When they looked again, they saw many more frogs scrambling out from behind the tree.
#c 他們再看，又有很多隻青蛙從樹後面湧出來。
#e The kid grabbed a frog, and put it on his hand.
#c 小孩抓起一隻青蛙，放在他的手上。
#e So he and his dog go home.
#c 他和他的狗便回家了。
#e Then, the rest of the frogs sat on the tree, looking at them. One of the frogs had been brought away (by the kid).
#c 接著，剩下的青蛙便坐在樹上，目送他們。其中一隻被(小孩)帶走了。
